### Onboard a new app into an existing use-case group

If `{{.use_case_group}}` already has its production branch in this workspace,
you only need to add a database:

```bash
python scripts/bootstrap_use_case_group.py \
    --project {{.use_case_group}} \
    --database new_app_db
```

Then scaffold the new app:

```bash
databricks bundle init https://github.com/{{.github_org_repo}}
# at prompts:
#   app_name: new-app
#   use_case_group: {{.use_case_group}}    ← same group, so it gets the same project
#   database_name: new_app_db                ← matches what bootstrap created
```

